1
00:01:33,226 --> 00:01:34,494
Let's give her a round of applause

2
00:01:34,694 --> 00:01:35,962
and congratulate Manager Ouyang

3
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:37,997
on ranking far ahead of everyone else

4
00:01:38,364 --> 00:01:40,166
as our undisputed top salesperson of the year.

5
00:01:41,968 --> 00:01:42,368
Great!

6
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:44,237
Amazing!

7
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:46,272
Congratulations! Congratulations!

8
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:47,607
Xiaohui, come up for a photo.

9
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,274
Okay, coming.

10
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:51,711
Three, two, one.

11
00:01:52,011 --> 00:01:52,345
Got it.

12
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:52,912
Okay.

13
00:01:54,047 --> 00:01:54,914
Wait, this is reusable?

14
00:01:54,914 --> 00:01:55,548
You scared me.

15
00:01:55,849 --> 00:01:56,149
What?

16
00:01:56,249 --> 00:01:56,883
Isn't it heavy?

17
00:01:56,883 --> 00:01:57,484
Let me hold it for you.

18
00:01:57,484 --> 00:01:57,784
No need.

19
00:01:58,084 --> 00:01:59,085
I want a photo too.

20
00:01:59,686 --> 00:02:00,186
Sure. Come on.

21
00:02:02,088 --> 00:02:02,522
Mr. Qin,

22
00:02:04,924 --> 00:02:05,892
she's a role model for all of you.

23
00:02:05,992 --> 00:02:06,693
Keep it up.

24
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:07,527
Congratulations.

25
00:02:15,201 --> 00:02:15,768
Do you know

26
00:02:15,768 --> 00:02:16,903
obesity makes people lazy?

27
00:02:17,237 --> 00:02:18,037
Look at Manager Ouyang.

28
00:02:18,838 --> 00:02:19,405
She's miles ahead.

29
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:21,808
Congratulations.

30
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:31,251
I'll transfer you some money.

31
00:02:31,551 --> 00:02:32,685
See what everyone wants to eat

32
00:02:32,719 --> 00:02:33,720
or drink. Order whatever you like.

33
00:02:34,287 --> 00:02:34,654
Okay.

34
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,991
Director, this is too much.

35
00:02:38,024 --> 00:02:39,225
There are only a few of us in the department.

36
00:02:39,559 --> 00:02:40,627
Keep the extra for yourself.

37
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:41,694
Don't my meals

38
00:02:41,728 --> 00:02:42,328
usually cost money too?

39
00:02:43,029 --> 00:02:44,030
It's still too much.

40
00:02:45,164 --> 00:02:45,999
Use it when you're on duty

41
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:47,033
to buy yourself a late-night snack.

42
00:02:47,367 --> 00:02:48,535
When I was a resident and fellow,

43
00:02:48,601 --> 00:02:49,068
my supervisors

44
00:02:49,135 --> 00:02:49,903
always covered my meals too.

45
00:02:51,404 --> 00:02:52,305
Thank you, Director.

46
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:06,586
Director Sheng.

47
00:03:06,853 --> 00:03:07,287
Director Zhou.

48
00:03:09,589 --> 00:03:10,890
I just saw the announcement.

49
00:03:11,891 --> 00:03:12,358
Congratulations.

50
00:03:13,693 --> 00:03:14,027
Thank you.

51
00:03:15,128 --> 00:03:16,095
At the meeting just now,

52
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:18,364
several senior directors were saying

53
00:03:19,432 --> 00:03:21,367
that not only do you come from a medical family

54
00:03:21,634 --> 00:03:22,569
and have a higher starting point than most,

55
00:03:22,969 --> 00:03:23,836
but you're also bold and competitive.

56
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:25,238
The younger generation is truly formidable.

57
00:03:26,472 --> 00:03:27,473
I'm only getting started.

58
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:29,209
I still have a lot to learn from my seniors.

59
00:03:30,109 --> 00:03:30,677
I can't be the one

60
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:31,811
holding the Heart Center back.

61
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,080
Now that your associate senior title is official,

62
00:03:34,547 --> 00:03:35,515
I suppose the word "acting"

63
00:03:35,682 --> 00:03:36,516
before your title

64
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:38,184
as department director

65
00:03:38,484 --> 00:03:38,985
can finally

66
00:03:39,085 --> 00:03:40,086
be removed, right?

67
00:03:40,787 --> 00:03:41,554
I hope you're right.

68
00:03:42,322 --> 00:03:43,122
But there's no rush.

69
00:03:43,489 --> 00:03:45,091
Retirement is still a long way off.

70
00:03:45,525 --> 00:03:46,326
I should be fine.

71
00:03:53,766 --> 00:03:54,434
Dr. Fang.

72
00:03:54,667 --> 00:03:55,435
Dr. Fang.

73
00:03:55,768 --> 00:03:56,536
Director Zhou asked me to bring you

74
00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:57,303
some afternoon tea.

75
00:03:57,503 --> 00:03:58,004
Thank you.

76
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,005
So much good food.

77
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:00,440
It's hot.

78
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:00,974
Thanks.

79
00:04:02,008 --> 00:04:02,842
A straw.

80
00:04:03,710 --> 00:04:04,210
Coffee.

81
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:06,079
Director Lin.

82
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:07,747
Director Lin.

83
00:04:09,215 --> 00:04:09,582
Here.

84
00:04:10,116 --> 00:04:10,550
Have some coffee.

85
00:04:10,850 --> 00:04:11,284
No, thanks.

86
00:04:12,352 --> 00:04:13,453
My life is bitter enough already.

87
00:04:15,154 --> 00:04:15,521
It's fine.

88
00:04:15,788 --> 00:04:16,556
Have something sweet.

89
00:04:18,391 --> 00:04:19,759
Nothing sweet can make me happy.

90
00:04:26,165 --> 00:04:26,733
People keep calling me

91
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:27,667
these past few days,

92
00:04:28,234 --> 00:04:29,836
saying they bought handmade items

93
00:04:29,836 --> 00:04:30,903
but still haven't received them.

94
00:04:31,037 --> 00:04:32,372
I'll forward the orders to you.

95
00:04:32,472 --> 00:04:34,274
You match them up and find the items.

96
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:47,053
There are so many. How am I supposed to find them?

97
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,055
They're all by the craft table.

98
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:52,425
The finished ones are in the second drawer.

99
00:04:52,525 --> 00:04:53,026
The unfinished ones

100
00:04:53,092 --> 00:04:54,093
are in the third drawer.

101
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:56,863
You have nothing to do anyway.

102
00:04:57,997 --> 00:04:58,364
Nothing?

103
00:04:59,198 --> 00:05:00,033
You're making work for me.

104
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:05,004
Fine. Disappear.

105
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:06,773
Take it and eat.

106
00:05:07,874 --> 00:05:08,808
Thank you, Dr. Fang.

107
00:05:09,942 --> 00:05:10,310
Run.

108
00:05:18,718 --> 00:05:19,585
Xiaoran.

109
00:05:20,453 --> 00:05:21,354
You and Xiaorui

110
00:05:21,354 --> 00:05:22,455
used to handle all this together.

111
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:24,824
And his workbench is

112
00:05:25,124 --> 00:05:26,225
more complicated than a heart.

113
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:27,627
How am I supposed to manage it alone?

114
00:05:28,428 --> 00:05:29,162
I can manage it.

115
00:05:29,195 --> 00:05:30,463
Why can't you?

116
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,068
Can we not do this?

117
00:05:36,803 --> 00:05:37,904
I've admitted I was wrong.

118
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:38,805
I've also done

119
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:39,639
everything you asked.

120
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:40,640
I know.

121
00:05:40,773 --> 00:05:41,641
You just think that

122
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,476
for every day I didn't come home before,

123
00:05:43,609 --> 00:05:44,844
you should stay away for a day too.

124
00:05:45,311 --> 00:05:46,145
By my count,

125
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:47,680
we're about even now.

126
00:05:49,048 --> 00:05:50,483
You think that's what this is about?

127
00:05:52,485 --> 00:05:53,453
I'm not counting on my fingers

128
00:05:53,486 --> 00:05:54,554
and keeping score with you.

129
00:05:54,587 --> 00:05:55,955
I'm not trying to make us even.

130
00:06:02,395 --> 00:06:02,929
Lin Yi,

131
00:06:04,597 --> 00:06:05,331
that's not

132
00:06:05,398 --> 00:06:06,132
what's wrong between us.

133
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,801
Of course it's not.

134
00:06:09,335 --> 00:06:09,936
Because between us,

135
00:06:09,936 --> 00:06:10,970
there is no problem at all.

136
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,308
I'm just tired.

137
00:06:20,446 --> 00:06:21,681
You work nonstop every day.

138
00:06:21,748 --> 00:06:22,648
Of course you're tired.

139
00:06:24,250 --> 00:06:25,685
So go home and get some rest.

140
00:06:26,986 --> 00:06:28,354
You'll sleep better at home.

141
00:06:33,693 --> 00:06:34,327
Xiaoran,

142
00:06:34,327 --> 00:06:35,628
what exactly do you want me to do?

143
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,532
I don't need you to do anything for me.

144
00:06:45,037 --> 00:06:46,105
I have surgery now.

145
00:06:47,006 --> 00:06:48,007
Then what should I do?

146
00:06:48,408 --> 00:06:49,275
Message me later,

147
00:06:49,609 --> 00:06:50,009
okay?

148
00:06:50,376 --> 00:06:51,644
I'll reply immediately.

149
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:53,846
My phone and watch are synced.

150
00:07:08,895 --> 00:07:09,495
Actually,

151
00:07:10,797 --> 00:07:11,931
no matter how good a relationship is,

152
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:13,399
it can't be sunny

153
00:07:13,432 --> 00:07:14,467
every single moment.

154
00:07:16,202 --> 00:07:17,703
Professor Peng and I are the same.

155
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:20,006
We're like...

156
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:21,607
like two trees

157
00:07:21,641 --> 00:07:22,875
growing side by side,

158
00:07:24,477 --> 00:07:25,444
rooted separately,

159
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:27,814
but with our branches and leaves intertwined.

160
00:07:29,682 --> 00:07:31,451
When one of us isn't doing well,

161
00:07:32,785 --> 00:07:34,587
we each take a step back

162
00:07:36,489 --> 00:07:38,591
and weather our own storm first.

163
00:07:40,827 --> 00:07:41,994
Then when we turn back,

164
00:07:42,829 --> 00:07:44,130
we've both become

165
00:07:45,331 --> 00:07:45,965
better,

166
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:50,002
more complete versions of ourselves.

167
00:07:57,343 --> 00:07:58,911
It's almost seven. Are you hungry?

168
00:07:59,145 --> 00:07:59,545
No.

169
00:07:59,812 --> 00:08:00,680
I ate late this afternoon.

170
00:08:01,147 --> 00:08:02,081
I told Sister Xia

171
00:08:02,281 --> 00:08:03,182
to save us a table.

172
00:08:04,517 --> 00:08:05,685
Why are you treating again?

173
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:06,485
It's my turn.

174
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:07,520
You're the top salesperson now.

175
00:08:08,087 --> 00:08:09,255
I couldn't have done it

176
00:08:09,322 --> 00:08:10,490
without your support.

177
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,392
I'll explain things to the family first.

178
00:08:13,526 --> 00:08:14,393
Let's meet at the entrance.

179
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:22,635
Hello, boss. What's up?

180
00:08:22,969 --> 00:08:23,970
Where are you?

181
00:08:23,970 --> 00:08:25,104
I've called you a million times.

182
00:08:26,205 --> 00:08:27,507
I was in surgery with Director Zhou

183
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,274
and didn't check my phone.

184
00:08:28,507 --> 00:08:29,075
What's wrong?

185
00:08:29,642 --> 00:08:30,376
You're at Dongli?

186
00:08:33,846 --> 00:08:35,481
I'm having dinner with Sheng Nian.

187
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:36,749
He suddenly messaged me this afternoon

188
00:08:36,782 --> 00:08:37,917
and finally softened up.

189
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:39,252
He said we could have dinner tonight.

190
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:40,386
This chance is rare.

191
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:40,953
Get over here now.

192
00:08:41,187 --> 00:08:41,921
Apologize properly

193
00:08:42,054 --> 00:08:42,855
and make amends.

194
00:08:43,789 --> 00:08:44,790
Tonight?

195
00:08:45,324 --> 00:08:47,593
I promised to celebrate with Director Zhou.

196
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:48,794
If I go,

197
00:08:48,794 --> 00:08:50,496
won't I just ruin everyone's mood?

198
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:52,598
Help smooth things over for me.

199
00:08:53,065 --> 00:08:54,667
Once Director Sheng cools down,

200
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,202
I'll apologize properly.

201
00:08:56,569 --> 00:08:57,770
I really shouldn't go tonight.

202
00:08:58,104 --> 00:08:58,838
This is exactly the kind of thing—

203
00:08:58,838 --> 00:08:59,171
Old Qin.

204
00:08:59,405 --> 00:09:00,172
What are you doing?

205
00:09:00,473 --> 00:09:01,073
Come inside already.

206
00:09:01,173 --> 00:09:02,208
Okay, okay. Right away.

207
00:09:06,078 --> 00:09:06,612
Fine.

208
00:09:06,846 --> 00:09:07,613
I'll stall him for you.

209
00:09:08,047 --> 00:09:09,115
Boss, you can do it.

210
00:09:09,482 --> 00:09:10,917
Thanks. Bye.

211
00:09:14,587 --> 00:09:15,087
Director Sheng,

212
00:09:15,922 --> 00:09:17,223
we sent the product to the OR

213
00:09:17,323 --> 00:09:18,925
before waiting for your final approval.

214
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:20,293
That was indeed our fault.

215
00:09:21,694 --> 00:09:23,195
Although Director Zhou's side

216
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:25,665
made a request

217
00:09:26,198 --> 00:09:26,799
that was difficult to refuse,

218
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:28,968
if I don't explain today—

219
00:09:29,201 --> 00:09:29,568
Director,

220
00:09:29,869 --> 00:09:30,570
I'll drink this.

221
00:09:39,478 --> 00:09:40,012
Mr. Qin,

222
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:41,314
what are you doing?

223
00:09:41,847 --> 00:09:43,149
You've already brewed two pots.

224
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:45,151
Old Qin,

225
00:09:45,318 --> 00:09:46,385
I have to say,

226
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,287
this Manager Ouyang from your company

227
00:09:48,321 --> 00:09:49,522
really has ideas.

228
00:09:50,556 --> 00:09:51,357
I heard

229
00:09:51,490 --> 00:09:52,792
she didn't even tell you first.

230
00:09:53,025 --> 00:09:54,560
She acted first and reported later.

231
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:57,196
Was she disrespecting

232
00:09:57,229 --> 00:09:58,631
her own boss,

233
00:09:58,965 --> 00:10:00,466
or Director Sheng?

234
00:10:01,334 --> 00:10:02,335
I... I...

235
00:10:02,735 --> 00:10:04,003
I failed to manage her properly.

236
00:10:04,437 --> 00:10:04,971
When I get back,

237
00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:06,305
I'll discipline her severely.

238
00:10:07,506 --> 00:10:08,240
Come on, eat.

239
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:08,708
Eat, eat.

240
00:10:08,975 --> 00:10:09,709
Is everyone here?

241
00:10:19,452 --> 00:10:20,052
Hello, boss.

242
00:10:20,252 --> 00:10:21,053
No, no, no.

243
00:10:21,754 --> 00:10:22,388
I'm telling you,

244
00:10:22,688 --> 00:10:23,589
there's no getting out of it now.

245
00:10:24,323 --> 00:10:25,625
You have to come today.

246
00:10:25,925 --> 00:10:26,625
Otherwise,

247
00:10:26,993 --> 00:10:28,894
Sheng Nian won't lift his glass

248
00:10:28,928 --> 00:10:29,562
or touch his chopsticks.

249
00:10:29,829 --> 00:10:30,563
We're stuck here.

250
00:10:31,063 --> 00:10:32,231
What am I supposed to do?

251
00:10:33,232 --> 00:10:34,433
You took the bonus,

252
00:10:34,867 --> 00:10:36,335
so you have to walk the plank too.

253
00:10:37,169 --> 00:10:37,970
What about Zhou Xiaofeng?

254
00:10:38,604 --> 00:10:39,271
Stand him up.

255
00:10:39,605 --> 00:10:41,007
Make up an excuse.

256
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,274
Ouyang, listen.

257
00:10:42,775 --> 00:10:43,709
With Zhou Xiaofeng,

258
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:44,910
we have the wind at our backs.

259
00:10:45,144 --> 00:10:46,512
Sheng Nian is different.

260
00:10:46,912 --> 00:10:48,214
We're rowing against the current.

261
00:10:48,481 --> 00:10:50,016
You need to pull hard on that oar.

262
00:10:50,282 --> 00:10:50,783
I don't care.

263
00:10:50,883 --> 00:10:51,684
You have to show up today.

264
00:10:51,851 --> 00:10:52,885
You hear me? Hurry.

265
00:11:02,428 --> 00:11:03,329
I'm sorry, Director Zhou.

266
00:11:04,130 --> 00:11:05,531
Looks like I have to cancel tonight.

267
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:07,667
What happened?

268
00:11:09,635 --> 00:11:10,770
I don't want to lie to you.

269
00:11:11,070 --> 00:11:13,039
Mr. Qin and Director Sheng

270
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:14,073
are having dinner,

271
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:15,875
and they want me there.

272
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,048
Sheng Nian asked you to go?

273
00:11:23,549 --> 00:11:23,849
Yes.

274
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:25,718
Don't go.

275
00:11:26,952 --> 00:11:28,187
It sounds like a trap.

276
00:11:28,721 --> 00:11:30,089
You'll only be asking for trouble.

277
00:11:31,323 --> 00:11:32,825
Of course I know it's a trap.

278
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:35,027
But I still have to bite the bullet and go.

279
00:11:35,494 --> 00:11:36,562
Unless I've decided

280
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,431
to stop doing business with Cardiac Surgery,

281
00:11:38,998 --> 00:11:40,533
I can avoid it today,

282
00:11:40,566 --> 00:11:41,734
but not forever.

283
00:11:44,170 --> 00:11:44,670
Director Zhou,

284
00:11:45,638 --> 00:11:46,772
I hope you can understand

285
00:11:46,772 --> 00:11:47,907
what it's like for working people

286
00:11:47,973 --> 00:11:49,208
trying to survive between two sides.

287
00:11:49,975 --> 00:11:50,242
How about this?

288
00:11:50,509 --> 00:11:51,711
I'll treat you to a big meal another day

289
00:11:52,011 --> 00:11:52,711
to make it up to you.

290
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,647
You don't have to be so formal with me.

291
00:11:57,750 --> 00:11:59,051
Then thank you for understanding.

292
00:11:59,385 --> 00:12:00,152
I'll go now.

293
00:12:00,786 --> 00:12:01,454
Thank you.

294
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,334
Director Sheng, I'm late.

295
00:12:15,634 --> 00:12:16,435
I'll punish myself with three drinks.

296
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,974
Manager Ouyang is certainly bold.

297
00:12:22,308 --> 00:12:23,642
No wonder you're in sales.

298
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:25,745
This second drink

299
00:12:25,811 --> 00:12:27,313
is still for Director Sheng.

300
00:12:28,013 --> 00:12:28,481
Director Sheng,

301
00:12:28,681 --> 00:12:29,949
please be magnanimous

302
00:12:30,116 --> 00:12:31,050
and overlook my mistakes.

303
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:31,851
Please forgive anything I did wrong.

304
00:12:32,151 --> 00:12:32,651
Here's to you.

305
00:12:35,521 --> 00:12:36,956
Manager Ouyang can really hold her liquor.

306
00:12:37,389 --> 00:12:38,390
But drinking from such a tiny glass

307
00:12:38,424 --> 00:12:39,191
isn't satisfying at all.

308
00:12:39,558 --> 00:12:40,326
Mr. Li.

309
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:41,994
What do you mean, hold my liquor?

310
00:12:42,194 --> 00:12:43,195
I really did arrive late,

311
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:44,330
so I feel bad.

312
00:12:44,663 --> 00:12:45,164
The third drink—

313
00:12:45,564 --> 00:12:45,831
come on.

314
00:12:46,465 --> 00:12:47,767
I owe both of you an apology too.

315
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,467
Seniors,

316
00:12:48,634 --> 00:12:49,135
if there's anything

317
00:12:49,135 --> 00:12:49,835
I haven't handled well,

318
00:12:49,835 --> 00:12:50,469
please bear with me.

319
00:12:50,970 --> 00:12:51,570
There's no need to apologize to us.

320
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:52,438
There's no need to apologize to us.

321
00:12:53,005 --> 00:12:54,273
Whether distributors

322
00:12:54,473 --> 00:12:55,574
or manufacturers,

323
00:12:56,008 --> 00:12:56,609
frankly speaking,

324
00:12:56,976 --> 00:12:57,877
we're all here

325
00:12:57,943 --> 00:12:59,311
to support clinical work

326
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:01,280
But there's one thing

327
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:02,681
I'm curious about.

328
00:13:03,082 --> 00:13:04,116
Artificial hearts,

329
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:04,984
no matter how you look at it,

330
00:13:05,050 --> 00:13:06,485
belong to Cardiac Surgery.

331
00:13:07,186 --> 00:13:08,354
So how did Manager Ouyang

332
00:13:08,521 --> 00:13:09,388
end up taking sides

333
00:13:09,655 --> 00:13:10,890
with Cardiology?

334
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:11,624
Sis,

335
00:13:11,924 --> 00:13:13,492
how can you joke with me like that?

336
00:13:13,526 --> 00:13:15,294
You really love teasing me.

337
00:13:15,427 --> 00:13:16,562
What sides?

338
00:13:16,562 --> 00:13:17,229
I'm not taking anyone's side.

339
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:18,831
When the clinical team makes a request,

340
00:13:19,031 --> 00:13:20,599
all we can do is carry it out.

341
00:13:21,033 --> 00:13:21,834
We don't understand

342
00:13:22,134 --> 00:13:23,135
the surgical plan anyway.

343
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:25,037
So what side is there to take?

344
00:13:26,005 --> 00:13:27,206
But since you brought it up,

345
00:13:27,239 --> 00:13:28,274
then it must be my problem.

346
00:13:28,407 --> 00:13:29,108
So I have to finish

347
00:13:29,208 --> 00:13:30,242
this drink too.

348
00:13:31,043 --> 00:13:31,644
Director Sheng,

349
00:13:31,944 --> 00:13:32,945
I'll finish mine. Drink as you like.

350
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:37,216
All right, eat something.

351
00:13:41,954 --> 00:13:42,454
Old Qin,

352
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:45,157
I remember what we said

353
00:13:45,191 --> 00:13:46,792
last time.

354
00:13:51,263 --> 00:13:54,333
This is what "three penalty drinks" really means.

355
00:13:56,735 --> 00:13:58,704
Those tiny glasses barely count as a warm-up.

356
00:13:58,804 --> 00:13:59,271
Right?

357
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:00,206
Oh, stop it.

358
00:14:00,272 --> 00:14:01,073
You were drunk last time.

359
00:14:01,073 --> 00:14:02,408
That was drunken talk.

360
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:03,209
It doesn't count.

361
00:14:03,475 --> 00:14:04,810
Besides, she's a young woman.

362
00:14:05,077 --> 00:14:06,679
She's never seen a scene like this.

363
00:14:08,113 --> 00:14:08,514
I'll drink.

364
00:14:09,315 --> 00:14:09,849
True.

365
00:14:10,115 --> 00:14:10,850
Actually,

366
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:12,551
there's no need to give us face.

367
00:14:13,085 --> 00:14:13,586
But

368
00:14:13,953 --> 00:14:15,254
Director Sheng was gracious enough to come today.

369
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:16,055
He's here,

370
00:14:16,722 --> 00:14:18,357
and after all the repeated invitations,

371
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:19,592
we finally got Manager Ouyang

372
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:20,559
to show up.

373
00:14:20,726 --> 00:14:22,127
She should show some sincerity.

374
00:14:22,127 --> 00:14:22,494
Right?

375
00:14:23,596 --> 00:14:23,996
Yes.

376
00:14:24,330 --> 00:14:24,763
This sincerity—

377
00:14:24,763 --> 00:14:25,164
give it to me.

378
00:14:27,666 --> 00:14:28,434
Mr. Li is right.

379
00:14:29,235 --> 00:14:30,636
I should drink these three.

380
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:32,404
I need to show my sincerity.

381
00:14:34,073 --> 00:14:34,907
As I said,

382
00:14:35,474 --> 00:14:36,875
please be magnanimous.

383
00:14:37,509 --> 00:14:38,844
If I did anything wrong,

384
00:14:39,311 --> 00:14:40,045
please bear with me.

385
00:14:40,679 --> 00:14:42,047
I'll drink all three.

386
00:14:53,592 --> 00:14:55,361
I told you Manager Ouyang was being modest.

387
00:14:55,527 --> 00:14:57,429
Look how decisively she drinks.

388
00:14:57,863 --> 00:14:59,198
Take it slow.

389
00:14:59,465 --> 00:14:59,932
Slowly.

390
00:15:00,032 --> 00:15:00,833
You just got here. Take it slow.

391
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:01,267
Sorry.

392
00:15:01,634 --> 00:15:02,768
Director Sheng,

393
00:15:02,968 --> 00:15:04,169
look how worried

394
00:15:04,203 --> 00:15:05,404
Mr. Qin is about her.

395
00:15:05,971 --> 00:15:06,805
Sis, don't joke like that.

396
00:15:06,805 --> 00:15:08,040
She really can't drink.

397
00:15:08,507 --> 00:15:08,874
Director,

398
00:15:09,275 --> 00:15:10,109
honestly,

399
00:15:10,209 --> 00:15:11,443
I've never seen her

400
00:15:11,510 --> 00:15:12,544
drink this much baijiu before.

401
00:15:13,145 --> 00:15:13,812
All right. Take a break.

402
00:15:14,213 --> 00:15:14,713
My turn.

403
00:15:15,281 --> 00:15:15,714
Director,

404
00:15:16,215 --> 00:15:17,583
I'll toast you with three too.

405
00:15:21,654 --> 00:15:21,954
Come on.

406
00:15:23,555 --> 00:15:24,256
Director Zhou.

407
00:15:36,969 --> 00:15:37,503
Director Zhou.

408
00:15:38,971 --> 00:15:39,471
Director Sheng.

409
00:15:42,174 --> 00:15:43,876
What a coincidence tonight.

410
00:15:44,209 --> 00:15:45,711
I've tried to arrange dinner with Director Zhou several times,

411
00:15:45,744 --> 00:15:46,645
but it never worked out.

412
00:15:47,046 --> 00:15:47,713
I just asked,

413
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,048
and he happened to be next door.

414
00:15:49,214 --> 00:15:51,083
So I thought, why wait for another day?

415
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:52,484
We might as well all have a lively evening together.

416
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:53,352
What a coincidence.

417
00:15:55,854 --> 00:15:56,255
Mr. Qin,

418
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:58,090
I hope we're not disturbing you.

419
00:15:58,891 --> 00:15:59,792
Not at all.

420
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,127
Having two great experts from Dongli

421
00:16:02,161 --> 00:16:03,128
here together

422
00:16:03,562 --> 00:16:04,363
is an enormous honor

423
00:16:04,396 --> 00:16:05,431
for me.

424
00:16:05,931 --> 00:16:06,832
Quick, give Director Zhou a seat.

425
00:16:06,999 --> 00:16:08,167
Yes, yes. Come, Director.

426
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:08,667
Director Zhou,

427
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:09,134
sit here.

428
00:16:09,268 --> 00:16:09,835
Here, here.

429
00:16:10,035 --> 00:16:10,469
No need.

430
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:11,403
I'll sit here.

431
00:16:15,007 --> 00:16:15,908
I came uninvited,

432
00:16:16,575 --> 00:16:17,142
so I brought my own pot.

433
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:28,053
Director Zhou,

434
00:16:28,387 --> 00:16:29,121
what a capacity.

435
00:16:33,592 --> 00:16:34,093
Director Sheng,

436
00:16:34,893 --> 00:16:35,627
this is our first drink together.

437
00:16:35,928 --> 00:16:36,395
Here's to you.

438
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:42,034
I'll finish mine.

439
00:16:42,468 --> 00:16:43,002
Drink as you like.

440
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:08,427
Director Sheng,

441
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:13,665
this way, please.

442
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:14,199
Director Sheng.

443
00:17:16,468 --> 00:17:17,569
Get some rest, Director Sheng.

444
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:18,203
Rest well.

445
00:17:27,012 --> 00:17:27,413
Director Sheng,

446
00:17:27,913 --> 00:17:29,214
please forgive our poor hospitality.

447
00:17:30,048 --> 00:17:30,416
You can go back.

448
00:17:31,250 --> 00:17:31,717
Director Sheng,

449
00:17:32,284 --> 00:17:33,452
I truly didn't know

450
00:17:33,485 --> 00:17:34,787
Zhou Xiaofeng would suddenly appear.

451
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:36,155
I swear.

452
00:17:36,522 --> 00:17:37,289
Of course I know.

453
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:38,357
You're not that stupid.

454
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:39,925
And you're no match for him.

455
00:17:41,627 --> 00:17:43,028
Get some rest when you get back.

456
00:17:43,595 --> 00:17:44,329
Drive carefully.

457
00:17:45,431 --> 00:17:46,432
Goodbye, Director Sheng.

458
00:17:46,532 --> 00:17:46,932
Goodbye.

459
00:17:58,010 --> 00:18:00,212
Money is hard to earn, and humiliation is hard to swallow.

460
00:18:01,346 --> 00:18:02,514
I don't understand.

461
00:18:03,348 --> 00:18:04,416
Why did Zhou Xiaofeng suddenly

462
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:05,484
message you,

463
00:18:05,784 --> 00:18:06,785
and why did you bring him over?

464
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:07,486
This...

465
00:18:08,153 --> 00:18:09,288
How would I know?

466
00:18:09,521 --> 00:18:10,022
He suddenly

467
00:18:10,122 --> 00:18:11,323
sent me a message.

468
00:18:11,623 --> 00:18:12,825
I still don't know

469
00:18:12,891 --> 00:18:14,426
how he knew we were here.

470
00:18:15,227 --> 00:18:15,961
Maybe

471
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:17,396
it was me.

472
00:18:18,864 --> 00:18:20,332
I posted on Moments

473
00:18:21,366 --> 00:18:22,034
with the location tagged.

474
00:18:55,234 --> 00:18:55,734
You're awake.

475
00:18:57,736 --> 00:18:58,804
Drink some honey water.

476
00:19:04,877 --> 00:19:05,611
Where are they?

477
00:19:07,412 --> 00:19:08,347
I drank them under the table.

478
00:19:12,684 --> 00:19:13,952
After all these years,

479
00:19:14,586 --> 00:19:15,354
how is your alcohol tolerance

480
00:19:15,354 --> 00:19:16,822
still so terrible?

481
00:19:17,789 --> 00:19:18,524
But your courage to drink

482
00:19:18,557 --> 00:19:19,725
is just like before.

483
00:19:24,396 --> 00:19:24,930
I'm sorry.

484
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,067
I didn't help and only made things worse.

485
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:33,005
Why did you put yourself through that?

486
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,107
Wasn't tonight's script

487
00:19:35,207 --> 00:19:36,775
supposed to be me going in alone?

488
00:19:39,211 --> 00:19:40,679
I started this.

489
00:19:41,747 --> 00:19:43,315
Of course I had to share the consequences.

490
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:45,484
That just means

491
00:19:45,684 --> 00:19:46,752
one more person got dragged in.

492
00:19:54,893 --> 00:19:55,427
I don't care

493
00:19:55,427 --> 00:19:56,328
how he treats me.

494
00:19:57,963 --> 00:19:59,531
Bowing my head and apologizing

495
00:20:00,165 --> 00:20:00,732
is no problem.

496
00:20:02,734 --> 00:20:03,769
But I can't tolerate him

497
00:20:06,305 --> 00:20:07,039
bullying you.

498
00:20:26,158 --> 00:20:26,825
Where are my glasses?

499
00:20:28,393 --> 00:20:28,794
Here.

500
00:21:04,329 --> 00:21:04,930
Sorry.

501
00:21:05,330 --> 00:21:06,331
I thought no one was here.

502
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:07,933
Sorry.

503
00:21:33,692 --> 00:21:34,359
I'll take you home.

504
00:21:35,127 --> 00:21:36,228
I drove too.

505
00:21:36,495 --> 00:21:37,429
The designated driver is almost here.

506
00:21:39,631 --> 00:21:40,198
Wait for me.

507
00:21:46,772 --> 00:21:47,673
This is my New Year's gift for Senlin.

508
00:21:47,673 --> 00:21:48,307
This is my New Year's gift for Senlin.

509
00:21:49,808 --> 00:21:51,009
Doesn't he like little animals?

510
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:52,310
I thought

511
00:21:52,310 --> 00:21:52,844
he might like this.

512
00:21:53,512 --> 00:21:54,479
You have good taste.

513
00:21:55,013 --> 00:21:56,515
You picked exactly what he'd love.

514
00:21:57,082 --> 00:21:57,949
He'll definitely like it.

515
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:00,085
Then on Senlin's behalf,

516
00:22:00,352 --> 00:22:01,186
thank you,

517
00:22:02,654 --> 00:22:03,155
You're welcome.

518
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:06,325
I've worked in sales for so long,

519
00:22:06,725 --> 00:22:07,793
but this is the first time

520
00:22:07,826 --> 00:22:08,994
I've received a return gift from a doctor.

521
00:22:10,562 --> 00:22:11,430
It's not from a doctor.

522
00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:18,437
I'll go now.

523
00:22:18,804 --> 00:22:19,104
Okay.

524
00:22:19,571 --> 00:22:20,472
Tell me when you get home.

525
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:32,718
Do you have plans for New Year's Eve?

526
00:22:34,152 --> 00:22:36,254
Dinner with my parents and Senlin.

527
00:22:39,224 --> 00:22:39,591
Okay.

528
00:22:40,392 --> 00:22:40,992
Happy New Year.

529
00:22:42,728 --> 00:22:43,328
But

530
00:22:44,262 --> 00:22:46,031
I'll be free after dinner.

531
00:22:50,635 --> 00:22:52,070
I know a nice bar-restaurant.

532
00:22:52,804 --> 00:22:53,572
Want to go together?

533
00:22:58,243 --> 00:22:58,810
My treat.

534
00:23:00,245 --> 00:23:00,712
Sure.

535
00:23:01,279 --> 00:23:02,147
It's a date.

536
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:22,200
I'm home.

537
00:23:22,768 --> 00:23:23,201
What about you?

538
00:23:45,524 --> 00:23:46,024
Dr. Fang,

539
00:23:46,358 --> 00:23:46,992
how about putting this here?

540
00:23:47,492 --> 00:23:47,959
Looks good.

541
00:23:48,126 --> 00:23:48,493
Okay.

542
00:23:51,930 --> 00:23:52,264
Xiao Fan,

543
00:23:53,031 --> 00:23:53,865
the head nurse is looking for you.

544
00:23:54,366 --> 00:23:55,400
Let me finish helping Dr. Fang first.

545
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:56,535
She seems to be in a hurry.

546
00:23:57,302 --> 00:23:57,936
All right.

547
00:23:57,969 --> 00:23:58,870
Then, Director Lin, please help.

548
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:04,709
Xiaoran,

549
00:24:05,410 --> 00:24:07,345
I can't sort out Xiaorui's orders.

550
00:24:07,479 --> 00:24:08,880
I can't find them no matter what.

551
00:24:10,782 --> 00:24:11,416
Could you

552
00:24:12,384 --> 00:24:13,552
come back and do it?

553
00:24:14,252 --> 00:24:15,253
Didn't I send you

554
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,054
the photos?

555
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,189
Just match them to the photos.

556
00:24:17,656 --> 00:24:18,223
I know,

557
00:24:18,356 --> 00:24:19,591
but I can't tell

558
00:24:19,724 --> 00:24:20,792
the photos from the actual items at all.

559
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:21,526
Every single one

560
00:24:21,526 --> 00:24:22,594
looks almost the same.

561
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:23,995
We need to ship them soon.

562
00:24:24,062 --> 00:24:24,796
It's already been delayed so long.

563
00:24:24,796 --> 00:24:25,597
If we delay again,

564
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:27,532
the customers will leave bad reviews.

565
00:24:33,505 --> 00:24:33,805
Fine.

566
00:24:34,272 --> 00:24:34,973
I'll come back tonight.

567
00:24:41,613 --> 00:24:42,147
You promised.

568
00:24:42,714 --> 00:24:43,315
When I get off work,

569
00:24:43,949 --> 00:24:44,683
I'll wait for you at home.

570
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:49,855
Director Lin,

571
00:24:50,455 --> 00:24:51,356
the head nurse wasn't looking for me.

572
00:24:52,123 --> 00:24:52,490
Really?

573
00:24:52,557 --> 00:24:53,825
Maybe she meant Xiao Yang.

574
00:24:54,292 --> 00:24:54,559
It's okay.

575
00:24:54,793 --> 00:24:55,327
Keep putting them up.

576
00:24:55,794 --> 00:24:56,561
Keep going. I didn't touch anything.

577
00:25:01,533 --> 00:25:02,167
You're back.

578
00:25:08,673 --> 00:25:09,241
What do I look like?

579
00:25:13,945 --> 00:25:14,446
Like what?

580
00:25:15,447 --> 00:25:16,448
Look at the whole thing together.

581
00:25:18,884 --> 00:25:19,551
I can't tell.

582
00:25:20,952 --> 00:25:22,354
Basking in the sunlight.

583
00:25:22,654 --> 00:25:23,555
A little sun.

584
00:25:28,493 --> 00:25:30,028
I printed all the orders.

585
00:25:35,567 --> 00:25:36,768
You found everything yourself?

586
00:25:37,969 --> 00:25:38,770
Yes. I had nothing to do this afternoon,

587
00:25:38,803 --> 00:25:39,871
so I sorted them all out.

588
00:25:40,872 --> 00:25:41,806
You don't need to handle them anymore.

589
00:25:43,975 --> 00:25:44,242
Okay.

590
00:25:44,342 --> 00:25:47,012
Then just match them

591
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:48,346
to these addresses and send them out.

592
00:25:49,047 --> 00:25:49,447
No problem.

593
00:25:50,048 --> 00:25:50,715
Leave them there.

594
00:25:50,849 --> 00:25:51,583
We can't ship them today anyway.

595
00:25:52,951 --> 00:25:53,184
Right.

596
00:25:53,718 --> 00:25:54,319
Come here.

597
00:25:54,886 --> 00:25:55,253
Over here.

598
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:56,388
Look. What's this?

599
00:26:02,694 --> 00:26:03,395
Is that me?

600
00:26:06,164 --> 00:26:07,365
You can actually tell?

601
00:26:08,366 --> 00:26:09,167
That proves I have

602
00:26:09,234 --> 00:26:10,201
a natural talent for knife work.

603
00:26:11,369 --> 00:26:12,604
They're all fruits you like:

604
00:26:13,071 --> 00:26:14,606
pineapple, blueberries, strawberries,

605
00:26:14,706 --> 00:26:15,373
and oranges,

606
00:26:15,574 --> 00:26:16,908
arranged into a little sun.

607
00:26:20,645 --> 00:26:21,479
Eat some fruit first.

608
00:26:21,913 --> 00:26:22,614
The food...

609
00:26:23,081 --> 00:26:23,348
The food.

610
00:26:36,328 --> 00:26:38,263
Thank you for the gift, Uncle Zhou.

611
00:26:38,563 --> 00:26:40,598
I really, really, really love it.

612
00:26:43,134 --> 00:26:44,235
You're welcome, Senlin.

613
00:26:44,569 --> 00:26:45,270
I'm glad you like it.

614
00:26:47,639 --> 00:26:49,374
Happy New Year, Uncle Zhou.

615
00:26:49,441 --> 00:26:50,442
I wish you good health.

616
00:26:55,914 --> 00:26:57,315
Happy New Year to you too.

617
00:26:57,716 --> 00:26:59,584
I hope you grow taller and stronger,

618
00:27:00,051 --> 00:27:01,119
and make more good friends

619
00:27:01,186 --> 00:27:02,320
in the new year.

620
00:27:02,887 --> 00:27:03,355
All done?

621
00:27:04,522 --> 00:27:05,624
Bye, Uncle Zhou.

622
00:27:05,624 --> 00:27:06,591
I'm going to brush my teeth.

623
00:27:17,369 --> 00:27:18,436
I'm getting ready to go out too.

624
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:19,471
See you soon.

625
00:27:26,277 --> 00:27:26,878
You made this?

626
00:27:28,346 --> 00:27:29,014
Of course not.

627
00:27:29,114 --> 00:27:30,148
How could I make something this good?

628
00:27:30,415 --> 00:27:30,949
I bought it.

629
00:27:32,083 --> 00:27:33,251
I made the seafood casserole.

630
00:27:33,585 --> 00:27:34,886
The seafood casserole is mine.

631
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,354
It'll be ready soon.

632
00:27:49,267 --> 00:27:49,834
You put these up?

633
00:27:51,036 --> 00:27:51,569
Yes, yes.

634
00:27:51,569 --> 00:27:52,470
I bought them this morning

635
00:27:52,604 --> 00:27:53,171
and put them up today.

636
00:27:53,571 --> 00:27:54,806
I wanted to change the atmosphere.

637
00:27:54,906 --> 00:27:55,840
New year, new beginning.

638
00:27:59,544 --> 00:28:00,078
A lot happened

639
00:28:01,913 --> 00:28:02,881
this past year.

640
00:28:04,015 --> 00:28:04,582
But it's a new year now.

641
00:28:05,517 --> 00:28:06,351
Let's leave the past

642
00:28:06,384 --> 00:28:07,052
in the past.

643
00:28:07,185 --> 00:28:08,953
We'll welcome the new year together

644
00:28:09,254 --> 00:28:10,155
and start a new chapter.

645
00:28:14,025 --> 00:28:15,126
I'm glad you've moved forward.

646
00:28:17,128 --> 00:28:17,495
Yes.

647
00:28:17,962 --> 00:28:18,363
And I think

648
00:28:18,396 --> 00:28:19,964
for movie night this year,

649
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:21,599
we shouldn't watch the old movie.

650
00:28:21,733 --> 00:28:22,467
Let's watch something new.

651
00:28:22,834 --> 00:28:24,736
They say 50 First Dates

652
00:28:24,769 --> 00:28:25,303
is really good.

653
00:28:26,004 --> 00:28:27,205
The heroine has amnesia.

654
00:28:27,572 --> 00:28:28,773
Actually...

655
00:28:37,048 --> 00:28:37,449
Oh no.

656
00:28:39,350 --> 00:28:40,118
I forgot, forgot, forgot.

657
00:28:41,453 --> 00:28:42,120
Where is it?

658
00:28:52,430 --> 00:28:52,797
Here.

659
00:28:54,199 --> 00:28:54,833
Xiaoran, can you

660
00:28:54,866 --> 00:28:55,533
help me?

661
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:56,634
I can't get this right.

662
00:28:56,868 --> 00:28:57,368
What is it?

663
00:28:57,969 --> 00:28:59,404
Come help me.

664
00:29:08,646 --> 00:29:09,748
These little ducks

665
00:29:10,448 --> 00:29:12,717
won't line up properly.

666
00:29:17,188 --> 00:29:18,957
There was a child who loved taking baths

667
00:29:19,524 --> 00:29:20,825
and liked playing with yellow rubber ducks

668
00:29:20,892 --> 00:29:21,893
while bathing.

669
00:29:22,794 --> 00:29:23,294
And

670
00:29:23,428 --> 00:29:24,562
he insisted on arranging all the ducks

671
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:25,430
in one straight row,

672
00:29:25,463 --> 00:29:26,397
perfectly aligned.

673
00:29:26,998 --> 00:29:28,633
But no matter what, they wouldn't line up.

674
00:29:29,534 --> 00:29:29,934
So

675
00:29:30,368 --> 00:29:31,903
he got upset and cried.

676
00:29:32,403 --> 00:29:33,404
He cried,

677
00:29:35,673 --> 00:29:36,875
"The ducks won't align."

678
00:29:37,075 --> 00:29:38,209
"They won't align."

679
00:29:38,409 --> 00:29:39,644
"They won't align."

680
00:29:43,214 --> 00:29:44,149
What did the little ducks' eyes

681
00:29:44,149 --> 00:29:44,883
look like?

682
00:29:46,785 --> 00:29:47,986
The ducks' eyes?

683
00:29:48,720 --> 00:29:49,354
They're plastic ducks.

684
00:29:49,921 --> 00:29:50,688
Not round or bright.

685
00:29:51,022 --> 00:29:52,090
So that means

686
00:29:52,557 --> 00:29:54,225
not round and bright—no forgiveness.

687
00:29:54,526 --> 00:29:55,360
No.

688
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:56,895
Don't refuse to forgive them.

689
00:29:57,529 --> 00:29:58,396
Our little ducks

690
00:29:58,429 --> 00:30:00,031
have eyes that are round and bright.

691
00:30:00,431 --> 00:30:02,800
So you have to forgive them.

692
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:06,171
It turns out

693
00:30:07,906 --> 00:30:09,841
they aren't ordinary little ducks.

694
00:30:10,875 --> 00:30:11,409
They're called...

695
00:30:11,943 --> 00:30:13,878
They're called misaligned ducks.

696
00:30:14,913 --> 00:30:15,680
Look, there are so many.

697
00:30:16,047 --> 00:30:16,948
Put them together and it's:

698
00:30:17,348 --> 00:30:20,552
misaligned ducks, misaligned ducks.

699
00:30:32,363 --> 00:30:33,231
Look at their eyes.

700
00:30:34,332 --> 00:30:35,366
They're round and bright.

701
00:30:36,134 --> 00:30:36,534
So

702
00:30:36,868 --> 00:30:37,402
they mean:

703
00:30:37,735 --> 00:30:40,238
forgive, forgive, forgive.

704
00:30:44,642 --> 00:30:45,310
Do you like them?

705
00:30:48,913 --> 00:30:49,681
I don't.

706
00:30:54,385 --> 00:30:55,887
I don't like hearing you say sorry.

707
00:31:07,165 --> 00:31:08,199
These days,

708
00:31:08,833 --> 00:31:10,001
no matter how busy work gets,

709
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:12,203
I'm always worrying about you,

710
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:14,405
always trying to control you.

711
00:31:15,707 --> 00:31:17,008
I know you're uncomfortable.

712
00:31:19,944 --> 00:31:20,812
I'm uncomfortable too.

713
00:31:24,916 --> 00:31:25,917
I don't like

714
00:31:26,751 --> 00:31:27,518
this version of myself.

715
00:31:32,223 --> 00:31:33,157
Our relationship right now

716
00:31:33,191 --> 00:31:34,125
isn't healthy.

717
00:31:42,533 --> 00:31:43,468
The seafood casserole is boiling.

718
00:31:44,135 --> 00:31:45,069
It's boiling.

719
00:31:46,504 --> 00:31:47,005
It's so hot.

720
00:31:47,905 --> 00:31:48,373
That's about right.

721
00:31:49,641 --> 00:31:50,441
Let's break up.

722
00:31:58,082 --> 00:31:59,584
Oh no. It's ruined.

723
00:32:00,184 --> 00:32:00,485
This is bad.

724
00:32:00,518 --> 00:32:01,085
I forgot to put fish balls

725
00:32:01,119 --> 00:32:01,953
in the seafood casserole.

726
00:32:01,986 --> 00:32:02,487
Without fish balls,

727
00:32:02,520 --> 00:32:03,488
how can it be a seafood casserole?

728
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:05,023
I'll... I'll go buy some.

729
00:32:05,189 --> 00:32:06,190
I'll go get fish balls.

730
00:32:06,291 --> 00:32:06,924
Lin Yi.

731
00:32:10,395 --> 00:32:11,262
Let's break up.

732
00:32:14,799 --> 00:32:15,566
I'm serious.

733
00:32:47,031 --> 00:32:47,432
Then...

734
00:32:50,001 --> 00:32:50,435
Then...

735
00:32:52,236 --> 00:32:52,503
Then...

736
00:32:54,172 --> 00:32:54,605
Then I guess

737
00:32:56,374 --> 00:32:57,308
there's no need to buy fish balls.

738
00:33:06,918 --> 00:33:07,285
Okay.

739
00:33:08,386 --> 00:33:08,987
If

740
00:33:09,887 --> 00:33:11,956
it makes you feel freer,

741
00:33:13,891 --> 00:33:14,826
I'm fine with it.

742
00:33:14,892 --> 00:33:16,194
I... I can accept it.

743
00:33:19,364 --> 00:33:19,664
Right.

744
00:33:22,367 --> 00:33:23,034
A new year.

745
00:33:24,135 --> 00:33:25,169
A new year, a new beginning.

746
00:33:25,703 --> 00:33:26,571
A new year, a new beginning.

747
00:33:26,637 --> 00:33:27,372
A new year, a new beginning.

748
00:33:27,372 --> 00:33:28,873
If...

749
00:33:31,709 --> 00:33:32,410
If this is

750
00:33:33,745 --> 00:33:34,712
your New Year's wish,

751
00:33:39,384 --> 00:33:40,184
I'll help make it come true.

752
00:33:48,793 --> 00:33:49,327
Let's both put down

753
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:50,595
our own burdens.

754
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:15,253
This way, please.

755
00:34:16,888 --> 00:34:17,355
Thank you.

756
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:18,623
You're here.

757
00:34:21,826 --> 00:34:22,560
Thanks.

758
00:34:26,864 --> 00:34:27,565
Have you been waiting long?

759
00:34:27,665 --> 00:34:28,066
No.

760
00:34:30,234 --> 00:34:31,169
What do you think of this restaurant?

761
00:34:31,502 --> 00:34:32,670
It's great. Beautiful.

762
00:34:34,205 --> 00:34:35,039
No wonder you're in sales.

763
00:34:35,306 --> 00:34:36,274
You know so many good places.

764
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:39,644
The night view here is wonderful.

765
00:34:39,844 --> 00:34:40,878
And at midnight,

766
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,146
there'll be fireworks.

767
00:34:42,713 --> 00:34:44,415
So I wanted to bring you here.

768
00:34:45,149 --> 00:34:46,083
A place this good

769
00:34:46,384 --> 00:34:47,185
must be hard to book.

770
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:51,322
I'm in sales, remember?

771
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:53,991
Did you order anything?

772
00:34:54,358 --> 00:34:55,126
No. I was waiting for you.

773
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:56,327
Okay.

774
00:34:59,130 --> 00:34:59,464
Here.

775
00:35:10,641 --> 00:35:11,042
Xiaoran,

776
00:35:25,156 --> 00:35:26,023
Happy New Year.

777
00:35:30,361 --> 00:35:31,162
Happy New Year.

778
00:37:35,853 --> 00:37:36,554
It's almost midnight.

779
00:37:38,456 --> 00:37:39,390
Time passes so quickly.

780
00:37:40,992 --> 00:37:41,892
Do you remember

781
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:42,960
when we were in college,

782
00:37:43,227 --> 00:37:43,928
we had a rule

783
00:37:43,928 --> 00:37:45,029
about midnight?

784
00:37:46,764 --> 00:37:48,532
No argument or anger could last past midnight.

785
00:37:49,200 --> 00:37:49,867
We had to turn the page.

786
00:37:52,570 --> 00:37:55,373
I really didn't expect you to remember.

787
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:00,711
People are interesting.

788
00:38:02,847 --> 00:38:03,948
When we were children,

789
00:38:05,282 --> 00:38:06,851
failing one exam

790
00:38:07,251 --> 00:38:08,919
or forgetting our red scarf

791
00:38:08,919 --> 00:38:09,520
and getting caught

792
00:38:10,054 --> 00:38:12,123
felt like the sky was falling.

793
00:38:13,291 --> 00:38:15,092
Then in our early twenties,

794
00:38:15,426 --> 00:38:16,394
we worried about school,

795
00:38:16,794 --> 00:38:17,695
worried about employment,

796
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:20,631
and feared the future.

797
00:38:21,465 --> 00:38:22,400
In relationships,

798
00:38:22,967 --> 00:38:24,602
even the smallest setback

799
00:38:25,169 --> 00:38:26,203
felt like life or death.

800
00:38:28,439 --> 00:38:29,407
Now,

801
00:38:30,274 --> 00:38:31,542
after life has beaten us up,

802
00:38:31,809 --> 00:38:32,910
we look back and think,

803
00:38:33,477 --> 00:38:34,345
what did any of that really matter?

804
00:38:36,113 --> 00:38:36,514
Exactly.

805
00:38:37,281 --> 00:38:38,883
After all, we're no longer

806
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:40,084
those carefree,

807
00:38:41,452 --> 00:38:42,853
unrestrained college students.

808
00:38:45,690 --> 00:38:46,891
At this stage of life,

809
00:38:47,391 --> 00:38:48,326
we have ties and responsibilities.

810
00:38:49,126 --> 00:38:50,327
We can't live only for ourselves.

811
00:38:51,629 --> 00:38:53,431
We live for the people

812
00:38:54,465 --> 00:38:54,999
and things we care about.

813
00:38:59,603 --> 00:39:00,838
No, I still have to ask you.

814
00:39:01,272 --> 00:39:02,773
What did it mean when Zhou Xiaofeng

815
00:39:02,773 --> 00:39:03,574
suddenly came to rescue you that night?

816
00:39:04,175 --> 00:39:04,909
I'll say the same thing again.

817
00:39:05,242 --> 00:39:06,310
If there's something between you two, that's fine.

818
00:39:06,544 --> 00:39:07,645
But in important situations,

819
00:39:07,645 --> 00:39:08,479
you still need to keep a low profile.

820
00:39:08,813 --> 00:39:09,814
Otherwise, how can we do business?

821
00:39:09,814 --> 00:39:10,114
Mom.

822
00:39:14,085 --> 00:39:14,685
What is it?

823
00:39:14,852 --> 00:39:16,120
I haven't told you yet.

824
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:17,955
Happy New Year.

825
00:39:20,591 --> 00:39:22,093
Happy New Year.

826
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:25,396
Next year, Mom will stay with you

827
00:39:25,596 --> 00:39:26,430
and keep fighting monsters together,

828
00:39:28,065 --> 00:39:28,733
okay?

829
00:39:31,602 --> 00:39:32,036
Go on.

830
00:39:33,504 --> 00:39:33,804
Come here.

831
00:39:33,971 --> 00:39:34,572
Dad, Mom,

832
00:39:35,473 --> 00:39:36,240
Happy New Year.

833
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:38,609
Happy New Year.

834
00:39:39,110 --> 00:39:40,144
They say family

835
00:39:41,045 --> 00:39:41,879
is both our armor

836
00:39:43,647 --> 00:39:44,348
and our weakness.

837
00:39:45,316 --> 00:39:46,684
It was for Senlin

838
00:39:47,752 --> 00:39:49,053
that I gave up clinical medicine

839
00:39:49,754 --> 00:39:50,888
and chose a career in sales.

840
00:39:52,123 --> 00:39:53,524
I have to keep going down this road.

841
00:39:54,024 --> 00:39:54,992
I can't give up,

842
00:39:55,893 --> 00:39:57,762
because I don't have the luxury of choosing.

843
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:00,164
I understand.

844
00:40:01,799 --> 00:40:02,800
Now,

845
00:40:03,467 --> 00:40:05,436
we have all kinds of titles before our names.

846
00:40:07,171 --> 00:40:07,605
Director Zhou,

847
00:40:08,305 --> 00:40:09,440
that night,

848
00:40:10,307 --> 00:40:12,276
the atmosphere got the better of us.

849
00:40:12,610 --> 00:40:13,644
A few rough men like us

850
00:40:13,677 --> 00:40:14,945
lost our sense of proportion

851
00:40:15,212 --> 00:40:16,480
and made a woman drink too much.

852
00:40:17,081 --> 00:40:18,482
Manager Ouyang is all right, isn't she?

853
00:40:18,816 --> 00:40:20,684
She surely isn't angry with us, right?

854
00:40:22,953 --> 00:40:23,320
She...

855
00:40:24,488 --> 00:40:25,456
She should be fine.

856
00:40:25,990 --> 00:40:27,558
And please don't be angry with us either.

857
00:40:28,325 --> 00:40:29,160
We overstepped.

858
00:40:29,493 --> 00:40:30,795
Please forgive us, Director Zhou.

859
00:40:31,328 --> 00:40:32,663
There's nothing to forgive.

860
00:40:33,230 --> 00:40:34,565
Please don't say that.

861
00:40:34,865 --> 00:40:36,567
You have to be magnanimous.

862
00:40:37,468 --> 00:40:39,904
If I'd known earlier about you and Manager Ouyang,

863
00:40:40,438 --> 00:40:41,005
you know,

864
00:40:41,405 --> 00:40:42,506
I never would've dared behave that way.

865
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:43,808
We're all constrained by circumstances.

866
00:40:44,842 --> 00:40:45,910
It's hard to escape

867
00:40:46,510 --> 00:40:47,845
the roles society gives us.

868
00:40:50,681 --> 00:40:52,016
When you came to the dinner

869
00:40:53,984 --> 00:40:54,752
that night,

870
00:40:54,785 --> 00:40:55,786
I was truly moved.

871
00:40:57,087 --> 00:40:58,055
Given your personality,

872
00:40:58,088 --> 00:40:59,290
it must have been very difficult

873
00:41:00,224 --> 00:41:01,358
for you to do that.

874
00:41:03,994 --> 00:41:04,695
Thank you.

875
00:41:07,231 --> 00:41:08,632
And I truly

876
00:41:09,934 --> 00:41:11,001
cherished

877
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:13,404
our cooperation over the past six months.

878
00:41:20,044 --> 00:41:20,611
Ouyang,

879
00:41:24,315 --> 00:41:25,649
I wanted to do more for you.

880
00:41:28,886 --> 00:41:29,854
But it seems this is

881
00:41:29,887 --> 00:41:30,855
as far as we can go.

882
00:41:35,893 --> 00:41:37,228
In the adult world,

883
00:41:40,364 --> 00:41:41,532
we can only tell the truth.

884
00:41:44,268 --> 00:41:45,369
We can't play dare anymore.

885
00:42:05,022 --> 00:42:05,689
What about you?

886
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:08,425
Do you like me?

887
00:42:13,330 --> 00:42:13,797
I do.

888
00:42:40,424 --> 00:42:41,025
Because between us,

889
00:42:41,025 --> 00:42:42,026
there is no problem at all.

890
00:42:43,093 --> 00:42:44,228
I'm just tired.

891
00:42:45,529 --> 00:42:46,764
I know you're uncomfortable.

892
00:42:48,132 --> 00:42:48,966
I'm uncomfortable too.

893
00:42:50,868 --> 00:42:51,835
Our relationship right now

894
00:42:51,869 --> 00:42:52,803
isn't healthy.
